fr.univLille.cristal.shex.validation

Class IntervalComputation

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.univLille.cristal.shex.schema.analysis.TripleExpressionVisitor<Interval>
      • fr.univLille.cristal.shex.validation.IntervalComputation

  • public class IntervalComputation
extends TripleExpressionVisitor<Interval>
    Allows to compute the interval for a triple expression and a bag. The Interval Algorithm is defined only for shape expressions that satisfy the following constraints: - Arbitrary cardinalities are allowed only on triple constraints. An "arbitrary" cardinality is one different from Interval.OPT, Interval.PLUS, Interval.STAR. - A Interval.PLUS cardinality is allowed only if the sub expression does not contain the empty bag. If the expression does not satisfy one of these, a IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
    Author:
    Iovka Boneva
